            __builder.AddMarkupContent(23, "<p><br></p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(24, "<p>The Celestial Year starts with Sagittarius rather than Capricorn because of the precession of the equinoxes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(25, "<p>Milankovich cycles cause the Earth&#39;s axis to wobble over thousands of years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(26, "<p>December 21st was around the beginning of Capricorn in Ancient Greek times</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(27, "<p>Now, however Capricorn only reaches the same location in the sky around January 18th.</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(28, "<p>The Age of Aquarius is the current time period now when the stars are shifted one month away from the time of the Ancient Greeks</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(29, "<p>We decided that the stars are more important than the seasons to an industrialized society, we want people to look up to mankind&#39;s future in the stars rather than look at agricultural practices.</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(30, "<p>The Celestial calendar will deviate from seasons in a 26,000 year cycle.</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(31, "<p>In about 6,000 years the year will begin in March rather than December.</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(32, "<p>As in that time the majority of people will not live on Earth, it doesn&#39;t matter that the seasons don&#39;t match the calendar anymore</p>\r\n");
            __builder.AddMarkupContent(33, "<p>Around every 150,000 years the Celestial Calendar gains 1 day of error relative to the Earth&#39;s movement through space</p>\r\n");
